# ===== BACKEND API CONFIGURATION =====

# Backend API URL (without /api suffix in some configs, with /api in others)
# For local development: http://localhost:5000/api
# For production (Railway): https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app/api
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# WebSocket URL (used for real-time chat)
# For local development: http://localhost:5000
# For production (Railway): https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app
VITE_WS_URL=http://localhost:5000

# ===== NOTES =====
# 1. These variables are embedded into the build at build time
# 2. Changes require rebuilding the frontend (npm run build)
# 3. For Vercel deployment:
#    - Update both URLs to point to your Railway backend
#    - Example: VITE_API_URL=https://student-notes-hub-production.up.railway.app/api
#    - Example: VITE_WS_URL=https://student-notes-hub-production.up.railway.app
# 4. Never commit this file with production values to git!
